;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Faithful\"\n| 2016\n| [[Drake (musician)|Drake]], [[Pimp C]]\n| ''[[Views (album)|Views]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"My Imagination\"\n| 2017\n| [[Majid Jordan]]\n| ''The Space Between''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Balance\"\n| 2017\n| [[Roy Woods]], [[PnB Rock]]\n| ''Say Less''\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of music videos as lead artist, with directors, showing year released\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Director(s)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"With Me/Do It Well\" \n| 2016\n| Jon Riera & LeSean Harris\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Too Deep\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017\n| Rohan Blair-Mangat\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Hallucinations\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| LeSean Harris\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Mood\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Morning After\"\n| 2018\n| Santiago Salviche\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"No Cryin\" \n| 2019\n| ?\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"A Muse\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2020\n| Andrew Hamilton\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Between Us\"\n| Brendan Vaughan\n|-\n\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n;Headlining\n* Debut Tour (2016)\n* Morning After (2018)\n;Supporting\n* [[Summer Sixteen Tour]] {{small|(with [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] & [[Future (rapper)|Future]])}} (2016)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/65039-drake-and-future-announce-summer-sixteen-tour/|title=Drake and Future Announce Summer Sixteen Tour|last=Yoo|first=Noah|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=April 25, 2016|accessdate=April 25, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Boy Meets World Tour]] {{small|(with Drake)}} (2017)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{SoundCloud}}\n*[https://www.instagram.com/dvsn DVSN on Instagram]\n*[https://www.twitter.com/dvsn DVSN on Twitte]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Black Canadian musical groups]]\n[[Category:Canadian musical duos]]\n[[Category:Canadian contemporary R&B musical groups]]\n[[Category:Contemporary R&B duos]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Toronto]]\n[[Category:OVO Sound artists]]\n[[Category:Warner Records artists]]\n", "text_old": "{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = dvsn\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image \n| Birthday         = November 17\n| caption          = \n| origin           = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| genre            = [[Alternative R&B]]\n| years_active     = 2015\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[OVO Sound]]|[[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[Drake (musician)|Drake]]|[[Majid Jordan]]|No\u00ebl Cadastre}}\n| website          = {{url|dvsndvsn.com}}\n| current_members  = * Daniel Daley\n* [[Nineteen85]]\n}}\n\n'''Dvsn''' (stylized as '''dvsn''' and pronounced \"division\") is a Canadian [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] duo, composed of singer Daniel Daley and producer [[Nineteen85]]. The duo is signed to [[OVO Sound]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2016/02/29/drake-signs-dvsn-to-ovo-sound/|title=Drake Signs dvsn to OVO Sound|work=[[Rap-Up]]|date=February 29, 2016|accessdate=February 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Music career==\n===''Sept. 5th''===\nOn September 5 2015, dvsn released two songs titled \"The Line\" and \"With Me\". They initially started gaining recognition when \"With Me\" was played on [[Apple Inc.|Apple]]'s Beats 1 radio during the seventh [[OVO Sound]] radio show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/listen-to-ovo-sound-radio-episode-7-featuring-partynextdoor-and-boi-1da-news.17989.html|title=Listen To OVO Sound Radio Episode 7 Featuring PARTYNEXTDOOR & Boi-1da|publisher=HotNewHipHop|last=Smith|first=Trevor|date=October 4, 2015|accessdate=October 4, 2015}}</ref> On December 2 2015, they released their third song, titled \"Too Deep\" on SoundCloud and the iTunes Store.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefader.com/2015/12/02/dvsn-too-deep|title=Lose Yourself In dvsn's \"Too Deep\"|work=[[The Fader]]|last=Leight|first=Elias|date=December 2, 2015|accessdate=December 2, 2015}}</ref> In March 2016, they released their fourth song, titled \"Hallucinations\" on [[SoundCloud]] and the [[iTunes Store]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nylon.com/articles/dvsn-hallucinations|title=Dvsn Will Give You Sexy, Holiday \"Hallucinations\"|work=[[Nylon (magazine)|Nylon]]|last=Gore|first=Sydney|date=December 24, 2015|accessdate=December 24, 2015}}</ref> On February 29 2016, it was announced that dvsn had signed to [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]'s OVO Sound record label.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.complex.com/music/2016/02/dvsn-signs-to-drake-ovo-sound|title=It Looks Like dvsn Has Signed To Drake's OVO Sound Label|publisher=[[Complex (magazine)|Complex]]|last=Ortiz|first=Edwin|date=March 1, 2016|accessdate=February 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn March 11, 2016, dvsn announced the release date of their debut studio album, titled ''[[Sept. 5th]]'', along with the album being made available for pre-order on the [[iTunes Store]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.complex.com/music/2016/03/ovo-dvsn-reveals-tracklist-release-date-artwork-for-upcoming-project-sept-5th|title=OVO's dvsn Reveals the Tracklist, Release Date, and Artwork for Upcoming Debut Album, 'Sept. 5th'|work=Complex|last=Mench|first=Chris|date=March 11, 2016|accessdate=March 11, 2016}}</ref> They released the album exclusively on the [[iTunes Store]] and [[Apple Music]] on March 27 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.complex.com/music/2016/03/dvsn-new-album-sept-5th-stream|title=dvsn's 'Sept. 5th' Album Is Finally Here|publisher=Complex|last=Diep|first=Eric|date=March 27, 2016|accessdate=March 27, 2016}}</ref> with the album releasing elsewhere on April 1 2016.\n\ndvsn made a guest appearance on Drake's fourth studio album, ''[[Views (album)|Views]]'' on the track titled \"Faithful\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/68822-dvsn-remix-drakes-faithful-listen/|title=dvsn Remix Drake\u2019s \"Faithful\": Listen {{!}} Pitchfork|website=pitchfork.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-08}}</ref>\n\n=== ''Morning After'' ===\nOn May 5 2017, dvsn released \"Think About Me\" as the lead single from their second album. A month later, \"Don't Choose\" was released as the second single. On August 9 2017, dvsn announced that ''[[Morning After (album)|Morning After]]'' would be the title of their next album. A new single, titled \"Mood\" was released on September 4 2017. The next day, dvsn revealed that the album will be released October 13 2017. ''Morning After'' was made available for preorder on September 22 2017.\n\nOn April 12 2019, DVSN made their first appearance at Coachella. The duo performed again on April 19, 2019 for Weekend 2 of Coachella.\n\n=== ''A Muse in Her Feelings'' ===\nOn July 10, 2019, they released two singles: \"Miss Me?\" and \"In Between\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dvsn-return-with-2-new-songs-listen/|title=dvsn Return With 2 New Songs: Listen|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> On October 30, 2019, they released \"No Cryin\" featuring [[Future (rapper)|Future]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dvsn-enlist-future-for-new-song-no-cryin-listen/|title=dvsn Enlist Future for New Song \"No Cryin\": Listen|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> They followed up this release by releasing \"A Muse\" and \"Between Us\" featuring [[Snoh Aalegra]]. On April 10, 2020, they released \"Dangerous City\" featuring [[Ty Dolla Sign]] and [[Buju Banton]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dancehallmag.com/2020/04/10/music/buju-banton-recruited-by-rb-duo-dvsn-ty-dolla-ign-for-new-track-dangerous-city.html|title=Buju Banton Recruited By R&B Duo Dvsn & Ty Dolla $ign For New Track \u2018Dangerous City\u2019|website=DancehallMag|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\ndvsn released their third studio album, ''A Muse in Her Feelings'', on April 17, 2020, via OVO Sound.<ref name=\"Muse\">{{Cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/dvsn-detail-new-album-a-muse-in-her-feelings-share-song-with-snoh-aalegra-listen/|title=dvsn Detail New Album A Muse In Her Feelings, Share Song With Snoh Aalegra|website=Pitchfork|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Studio albums, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Album details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"5\"| Peak chart positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Canadian Albums Chart|CAN]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6904264/dvsn/chart?f=309|title=Dvsn \u2013 Chart history: Canadian Albums|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=April 5, 2016}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"| [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK<br />R&B]]<br /><ref>Peak chart positions for albums on the R&B Chart in the United Kingdom:\n* ''Sept. 5th'': {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-albums-chart/20160408/115/|title=Official R&B Albums Chart Top 40 \u2013 08 April 2016 \u2013 14 April 2016|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=April 8, 2016}}\n* ''Morning After'': {{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-albums-chart/20171020/115/|title=Official R&B Albums Chart Top 40 \u2013 20 October 2017 \u2013 26 October 2017|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=October 20, 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Billboard 200|US]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/dvsn/chart-history/billboard-200|title=Dvsn \u2013 Chart history: Billboard 200|work=Billboard|accessdate=October 24, 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|US<br />R&B<br />/HH]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6904264/dvsn/chart?f=333|title=Dvsn \u2013 Chart history: R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=April 5, 2016}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[R&B Albums|US<br />R&B]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/6904264/dvsn/chart?f=1235|title=Dvsn \u2013 Chart history: R&B Albums|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|accessdate=April 5, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Sept. 5th]]''\n|\n* Released: March 27, 2016<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/sept.-5th/id1091615564|title=SEPT. 5TH by dvsn|work=[[iTunes Store]]|publisher=[[Apple Inc.|Apple]]|accessdate=March 11, 2016}}</ref>\n* Label: [[OVO Sound]], [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n* Formats: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[LP record|LP]], [[Music download|digital download]]\n| 69 || 25 || 133 || 17 || 7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Morning After (album)|Morning After]]''\n|\n* Released: October 13, 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://instagram.com/p/BXRGm9cDSAW/|title=Instagram post by dvsn \u2022 Aug 1, 2017 at 10:03pm UTC|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2017-08-02}}</ref>\n* Label: OVO Sound, Warner Bros.\n* Formats: CD, LP, digital download\n| 19 || 30 || 38 || 22 || 6\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''A Muse in Her Feelings''\n|\n* Released: April 17, 2020<ref name=\"MuseAM\">{{Cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/a-muse-in-her-feelings/1503181571|title=\u200eA Muse In Her Feelings by dvsn on Apple Music|via=[[Apple Music]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* Label: OVO Sound, Warner Bros.\n* Formats: CD, LP, digital download\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:10em;\